sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Dashboard
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as ODH Notebook Webhook<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS mTLS
    participant Controller as ODH Notebook Controller<br/>Watch Loop
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuthProxy as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuthServer as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Notebook as Notebook Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 1: Notebook Creation (OAuth Mode)

    User->>K8sAPI: CREATE Notebook CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Mutating Webhook Call<br/>mTLS (Client Cert)
    Webhook->>Webhook: Inject OAuth sidecar<br/>+ reconciliation lock annotations
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response (patched spec)

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch Notebook CRDs<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Notebook CREATE event

    Controller->>K8sAPI: CREATE ServiceAccount<br/>TLS1.2+ / SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: CREATE OAuth Secret<br/>TLS1.2+ / SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: CREATE Service (8443/TCP)<br/>TLS1.2+ / SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: CREATE Route (Reencrypt)<br/>TLS1.2+ / SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: CREATE NetworkPolicies<br/>TLS1.2+ / SA Token

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 2: Notebook Access (OAuth Mode)

    User->>Router: HTTPS Request<br/>443/TCP TLS1.2+
    Router->>OAuthProxy: Forward to Pod<br/>8443/TCP TLS1.2+ (Reencrypt)

    OAuthProxy->>OAuthProxy: Check session cookie
    OAuthProxy->>OAuthServer: Initiate OAuth flow<br/>443/TCP HTTPS / SA Token
    OAuthServer-->>User: Redirect to login page
    User->>OAuthServer: Authenticate<br/>User Credentials

    OAuthServer->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>Check: user can GET Notebook CR
    K8sAPI-->>OAuthServer: Authorization result

    OAuthServer-->>User: OAuth callback with token
    User->>OAuthProxy: Request with OAuth token
    OAuthProxy->>OAuthProxy: Validate & create session cookie
    OAuthProxy->>Notebook: Proxy to notebook<br/>localhost:8888 HTTP
    Notebook-->>OAuthProxy: Jupyter UI response
    OAuthProxy-->>Router: HTTPS Response
    Router-->>User: Jupyter Notebook UI

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 3: Non-OAuth Mode (simplified)

    User->>Router: HTTPS Request<br/>443/TCP TLS1.2+
    Router->>Notebook: Forward to Pod<br/>8888/TCP HTTP (Edge TLS)
    Notebook-->>Router: Jupyter UI response
    Router-->>User: Jupyter Notebook UI
